<p><em>Serves God knows how many, takes 2-3 hours</em></p>

<p>What makes this recipe so cool is its ability to take quite some time and then saves large volumes of it down the road. I have been saved by this recipe, praised about this recipe, and surprised by this recipe countless time</p>

<h3 id="ingredients">Ingredients</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Pointed red paprika</li>
  <li>Tomatoes</li>
  <li>Red onion (with tunic intact)</li>
  <li>Fennel</li>
  <li>Garlic</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="instructions">Instructions</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Heat the oven to 180Â°C</li>
  <li>Cut paprika, fennel and red onion length-wise</li>
  <li>Roast for 2 or 3 hours</li>
</ul>
